						<summary>

						<p>Slab in front of the Rājarājēśvari temple.</p>						

						<p>7th-8th century A.D. </p>						

						<p>This inscription engraved in characters of about 7th-8th century A.D., states that Arākoli entered fire becoming a victim of calumny at Taḻekāḍu. The memorial stone in his honour was set up by Palyavaṇa Aḍigānapa and Malaloṇḍaiyya.</p>						

						</summary>
